mutism, catatonia, stupor, coma, agitation, confusion, hallucinations, delusions), autonomic instability, restlessness, rigidity, ataxia, myoclonus, hyperreflexia, tremors, diaphoresis, elevated creatine phosphokinase levels, and hyperpyrexia. Patients should seek prompt medical attention if they experience symptoms that could indicate the occurrence of torsade de pointes such as dizziness, lightheadedness, fainting, palpitation, irregular heart rhythm, shortness of breath, or syncope.', 'Synergism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/84361/', '[1] "Product Information. Austedo (deutetrabenazine)." Teva Pharmaceuticals USA, North Wales, PA.', 1767365205);
